JOHANNESBURG - As the death of another Life Esidimeni patient is confirmed, Health Minister Aaron Motsoaledi has appointed an ad hoc independent tribunal to process all appeals relating to the Health Ombudsman's report into the tragedy.Over 100 mentally-ill patients died after being transferred from Life Esidimeni to several unlicensed NGOs.READ: Esidimeni patients moved to new homeThe tribunal will be headed by the retired Judge President of the North Gauteng High Court, Bernard Ngoepe.The tribunal is expected to conclude the appeal process within two months.eNCA